The paper proposes a multi-agent framework for distributed coordination in solving linear equations, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses communication and coordination among agents, which are key topics in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of consensus and conservation mechanisms to achieve distributed solution of a linear equation involves control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of simulations to validate the proposed algorithms, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithms, which involves machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
